@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Starter app</p>
    <h1>Basic Blazor Server setup with SQL Server</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        This project is wired for interactive server-side components, EF Core, and a SQL Server-backed
        <code>ApplicationDbContext</code>.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
        <h2>Database</h2>
        <p>
            Update the <code>DefaultConnection</code> string in <code>appsettings.json</code>, create a migration,
            and apply it to your SQL Server instance.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
        <h2>Sample data flow</h2>
        <p>
            The <a href="/todos">Todos</a> page loads, inserts, toggles, and deletes records through EF Core.
        </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
        <h2>Project shape</h2>
        <p>
            The UI lives under <code>Components</code> and the EF Core types live under <code>Data</code>.
        </p>
    </article>
</section>

